.TH F00-CAT 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00-cat \- concatenate files and print on the standard output (f00 suite)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00-cat
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Concatenate FILE(s) to standard output. Pure assembly. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode. \fB--core\fR selects strict GNU cat-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.B \-A \-b \-e \-E \-n \-s \-t \-T \-u \-v
and long forms. See \fBf00-cat --help\fR.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-\-headers\fR / \fB\-\-no\-headers\fR
file banners when multiple files
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
detailed JSON summary
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
detailed CSV summary
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cat (1),
.BR f00-ls (1)
